headline: Why KeyCorp (KEY) Stock Is Down Today
summary: Shares of regional banking company KeyCorp (NYSE:KEY) fell 2.6% in the afternoon session after a broad market downturn was triggered by a court ruling that deemed most of President Trump's tariffs illegal.
